  "chapters": [
    {
      "number": 1,
      "summary": "Chapter 1 of Philemon",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_1",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 1,
          "text": "Paul, a prisoner of Christ Jesus, and Timothy our brother,\nTo Philemon our beloved friend and fellow laborer,",
          "paragraph": 1,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_2",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 2,
          "text": "to the beloved Apphia, Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church in your house:",
          "paragraph": 1,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_3",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 3,
          "text": "Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.",
          "paragraph": 1,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_4",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 4,
          "text": "I thank my God, making mention of you always in my prayers,",
          "paragraph": 1,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_5",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 5,
          "text": "hearing of your love and faith which you have toward the Lord Jesus and toward all the saints,",
          "paragraph": 1,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_6",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 6,
          "text": "that the sharing of your faith may become effective by the acknowledgment of every good thing which is in you in Christ Jesus.",
          "paragraph": 2,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_7",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 7,
          "text": "For we have great joy and consolation in your love, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed by you, brother.",
          "paragraph": 2,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_8",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 8,
          "text": "Therefore, though I might be very bold in Christ to command you what is fitting,",
          "paragraph": 2,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_9",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 9,
          "text": "yet for love’s sake I rather appeal to you—being such a one as Paul, the aged, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ—",
          "paragraph": 2,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_10",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 10,
          "text": "I appeal to you for my son Onesimus, whom I have begotten while in my chains,",
          "paragraph": 2,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_11",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 11,
          "text": "who once was unprofitable to you, but now is profitable to you and to me.",
          "paragraph": 3,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_12",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 12,
          "text": "I am sending him back. You therefore receive him, that is, my own heart,",
          "paragraph": 3,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_13",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 13,
          "text": "whom I wished to keep with me, that on your behalf he might minister to me in my chains for the gospel.",
          "paragraph": 3,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_14",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 14,
          "text": "But without your consent I wanted to do nothing, that your good deed might not be by compulsion, as it were, but voluntary.",
          "paragraph": 3,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_15",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 15,
          "text": "For perhaps he departed for a while for this purpose, that you might receive him forever,",
          "paragraph": 3,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_16",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 16,
          "text": "no longer as a slave but more than a slave—a beloved brother, especially to me but how much more to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord.",
          "paragraph": 4,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_17",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 17,
          "text": "If then you count me as a partner, receive him as you would me.",
          "paragraph": 4,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_18",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 18,
          "text": "But if he has wronged you or owes anything, put that on my account.",
          "paragraph": 4,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_19",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 19,
          "text": "I, Paul, am writing with my own hand. I will repay—not to mention to you that you owe me even your own self besides.",
          "paragraph": 4,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_20",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 20,
          "text": "Yes, brother, let me have joy from you in the Lord; refresh my heart in the Lord.",
          "paragraph": 4,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_21",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 21,
          "text": "Having confidence in your obedience, I write to you, knowing that you will do even more than I say.",
          "paragraph": 5,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_22",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 22,
          "text": "But, meanwhile, also prepare a guest room for me, for I trust that through your prayers I shall be granted to you.",
          "paragraph": 5,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_23",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 23,
          "text": "Epaphras, my fellow prisoner in Christ Jesus, greets you,",
          "paragraph": 5,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_24",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 24,
          "text": "as do Mark, Aristarchus, Demas, Luke, my fellow laborers.",
          "paragraph": 5,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        },
        {
          "id": "nkjv_philemon_1_25",
          "translation": "NKJV",
          "book": "philemon",
          "bookName": "Philemon",
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 25,
          "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.",
          "paragraph": 5,
          "speaker": "Narrator",
          "isRedLetter": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}